About

  • August 2012

    Rochester Institute of Technology

    In 2012, I entered into my freshman year at RIT. I began as a computer science major, but by the end of the year had switched to our software engineering program.

  • June 2013

    General Dynamics Advanced Information Systems

    After my sophomore year at RIT, I worked as an intern at GDAIS, on an internal research and development team working with quantum computers. Here I was able to improve my Python skills, as well as understand and learn quite a bit about quantum mechanics and also on a lower level, how regular computers work.

  • May 2014

    Kappa Delta Rho

    This year I came to the realization that I wanted an opportunity to improve my leadership abilities, as well as do more service around the Rochester area. I seeked out and joined the fraternity of Kappa Delta Rho, and was almost immediately put in charge of fundraising for the chapter. In my time as fundraising chair, I organized multiple fundraisers, including a Dancing With the Stars-esque event we called Dancing with the Greeks.

  • January 2015

    EnerNOC

    I joined the Big Data and Analytics team at EnerNOC for a second co-op term. Here I worked using Scala, Twitter Finagle, Javascript, Apache Storm, and various other technologies to create an interface for accessing information that was coming into our systems.

  • June 2015

    CoverMyMeds

    This is an up and coming tech startup that I had the privilege of interning at for seven months. I worked mostly in Ruby on Rails and Python/CherryPy frameworks, to integrate our systems with different pharmacies. This is all in an effort to make the prior authorization process of prescription fulfillment easier and faster.

The Big Man from the Big Man's World food blog already had his site up and running, but he needed me for various questions regarding maintenance. I led him to set up caching for advertisements to speed up response time, as well as fixed a database error some of his users were experiencing.
